{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"13adc79a-88c2-4c90-b8ea-dd2f3598245b","content":"Here's what I created and what you still need to do:\n\n### Created: `.github/workflows/publish.yml`\n- Triggers on GitHub **release published** events\n- Requests an OIDC `id-token` (the key permission for trusted publishing)\n- Packs and pushes to nuget.org **with no API key** — NuGet authenticates via the OIDC token automatically\n\n### You must configure NuGet.org (one-time):\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Add a Trusted Publisher**\n2. Select **GitHub Actions** as the provider\n3. Fill in:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you add a GitHub environment)*\n4. Save\n\nAfter that, any run of this workflow will authenticate automatically via OIDC — no secrets or API keys needed. The `dotnet nuget push` command picks up the federated token from the Actions runtime automatically when `id-token: write` is set and a matching trusted publisher exists on nuget.org.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b2541300-b5be-4bad-916d-698b1939a467","outputTokens":268,"requestId":"C00C:38B4C:122960:15B257:69EABEA0"},"id":"f7c816d3-2cab-4cec-b082-f2d5df77eefd","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:52.461Z","parentId":"eda58d5b-ed3e-4c63-8dc9-784b49e1eb69"}
